description.narrative: In 2021, the HSS Unit focused on supporting countries in advocating for technical and financial resources for protecting, equitable and resilient health systems to ensure the continuity of health services during the Covid-19 pandemic. ;Main support was geared toward reviewing of national policies and strategies, including the essential health package, national capacity development and influencing domestic resource mobilization and allocations. In addition to leveraging strategic partnerships to advance PHC agenda. Focus was also on evidence generation and experience sharing to address the issues of health service continuity in health emergencies and other health outbreaks.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:16/02/2022
